---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const pageName = "Daniel Checketts"
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageName}>
	<div class="space-y-16">
		<section
			id="welcome-banner"
			class=" overflow-hidden">

			<div
				id="welcome-banner-content"
				class="surface-card bg-stone-50 p-4 shadow-sm relative grid gap-8 p-6 md:grid-cols-[auto,1fr] md:items-center md:p-10">
				<div id="image-card">
					<img
						src="/img/daniel-checketts-2025.jpg"
						alt="Photo of Daniel Checketts"
						class="h-40 w-40 rounded-full object-cover ring-4 ring-white"
					/>
					<span class="mt-3 block text-center text-sm text-stone-600">Me, Circa Late 2025</span>
				</div>

				<div id="welcome-banner-message" class="space-y-4 max-w-2xl">
					<span class="pill">Welcome!</span>
					<h1 class="page-heading">Hi, my name is Daniel Checketts, and I love writing code.</h1>
					<a href="/learn" class="button-primary">Start Learning</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section id="about" class="surface-card p-6 shadow-sm md:p-8">
			<div class="space-y-4">
				<p class="text-base leading-7 text-stone-700">Computers have always been in my DNA—my dad graduated from BYU-Idaho in Computer Information Technology and programmed throughout my childhood. While middle and high school computer classes didn't quite capture my imagination, everything changed when I arrived at BYU-I myself.</p>
				<p class="text-base leading-7 text-stone-700">In an Intro to Programming course, I fell in love with Python. The class taught simple concepts like loops and logic gates, gave us a desired outcome, and granted us unlimited freedom to achieve it. That open-ended puzzle-solving hooked me.</p>
				<p class="text-base leading-7 text-stone-700">My path wasn't entirely linear; educational hardships initially pushed me away from my dad's exact degree track. However, while serving a mission for The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints, I found clarity. My mission gave me perspective on what I truly valued in my education, alongside unique opportunities to serve others using my technical instincts. For instance, when a temporary bug in Facebook Messenger began distorting shared links to vital tools like Google Forms and Sheets, I was able to help my friends by manually decrypting the broken links, translating the scrambled hexadecimal values into ASCII characters to recover the usable URLs.</p>
				<p class="text-base leading-7 text-stone-700">Today, I am pursuing my BS in Web Design &amp; Development.</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section id="project-showcase" class="space-y-6">
			<h2 class="section-heading">Projects</h2>
			<ul class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
				<li class="surface-card surface-card-hover">
					<a href="https://github.com/dchecketts/dchecketts.github.io" class="block h-full p-5 text-stone-900 no-underline">
						<div class="space-y-2">
							<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight">Personal Website</h3>
							<p class="text-sm leading-6 text-stone-600">This site, built with Astro, Tailwind, and HTMX.</p>
						</div>
					</a>
				</li>

				<li class="surface-card surface-card-hover">
					<a href="https://github.com/dchecketts/vite-site-template" class="block h-full p-5 text-stone-900 no-underline">
						<div class="space-y-2">
							<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight">Vite Site Template</h3>
							<p class="text-sm leading-6 text-stone-600">A starter template for quickly spinning up sites.</p>
						</div>
					</a>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>